Avoid the 'filter' tool; it consistently lowers the value and introduces 'botched filtering' or 'botched extraction'.

The Vial (ğŸ§ª) works best on items made from two SOLID ingredients (e.g., solid-magical + solid-magical), transforming them into a 60-value liquid extract. Avoid using the Vial on GAS items. The Filter (ğŸ§«) works best on items made from two LIQUID ingredients (e.g., liquid-magical + liquid-magical) or on items combining a LIQUID and a GAS ingredient. This typically yields a 60-value filtered liquid. Be cautious using the Filter on items containing 'botched' features or solid components.
